@d1 1
a1 1
.\"	$OpenBSD: pninek.4,v 1.6 2007/02/25 20:16:23 jmc Exp $
d28 1
a28 1
.Dd $Mdocdate$
d36 1
a36 1
.Cd "pninek0 at sbus? flags 0x0"
a80 15
.Pp
The
.Nm
driver supports hardware acceleration to erase the screen and scroll text.
By default, acceleration is
.Em not
enabled.
By setting
.Ar flags
to 1
(via
.Xr config 8
or
.Xr boot_config 8 )
this acceleration can be enabled.
d102 1
a102 3
.Xr zx 4 ,
.Xr boot_config 8 ,
.Xr config 8
d107 3
a109 1
It is not possible to change resolutions.
@


